# # Section 2. Three Common LLM Tasks
# 
# We have the folowing LLM Tasks:
#  - Classification
#  - Summarization
#  - Extraction
# 
# For each task, we will explore Prompt Engineering techniques that we can apply to improve the responses from our LLMs.
# 

# %% [markdown]
# ## 2.1 Classification
# 
# For classification, we will explore the following techniques.
# 
# | Technique | Description | Use Case |
# | --------- | ----------- | -------- |
# | Zero-shot | Query the LLM without giving examples | For simple or general tasks; lower token usage |
# | Few-shot  | Provide 2-5 examples to LLM | For expecting strict input/output formats |
# | CoT       | Instruct it to reason step-by-step | For complex tasks; reduces hallucination |
# | Role-based| Instruct it to answer with a persona | Used for setting conversational tone |

# %% [markdown]
# ### 2.1.1 Zero-shot Classification
# 
# If you try running the following multiple times, you will see that the answer sometimes changes drastically.
# 

# %%
ChatWrapper(
  user_prompt = "This vacuum looks good at first but broke after 3 weeks, I hate it.",
  system_prompt = "Classify this review as positive, negative, or neutral",
  model="gemma3:1b"
)
print()

ChatWrapper(
  user_prompt = "This vacuum looks good at first but broke after 3 weeks, I hate it.",
  system_prompt = "Classify as bad, good, or neutral",
  model="gemma3:1b"
)
print()

ChatWrapper(
  user_prompt = "This vacuum looks good at first but broke after 3 weeks, I hate it.",
  system_prompt = "Classify as happy, sad, or angry",
  model="gemma3:1b"
)

