# %% [markdown]
# ## 2.2 Summarization
# 
# Summarization is a common task in Natural Language Processing. This can be used to simplify large amounts of text for human consumption, but modern Agentic Systems can also summarize the output of one agent and feed it as input to another agent.
# 
# We will be talking about 4 main summarization strategies.
#  - Basic Summarization
#  - Constrained Summarization
#  - Chain-of-Thought Summarization
#  - Role-based Summarization

# %% [markdown]
# ### 2.2.1 Basic Summarization
# 
# We basically just do a simple system prompt for the LLM and directly tell it to summarize.

# %%
ChatWrapper(
  user_prompt = """
  - This machine has more pull than a politician during election season.
  - Finally, a vacuum that sucks at its job in the best way possible.
  - It’s so quiet I actually had to check if it was still turned on.
  - Sleek, powerful, and makes me feel significantly more like a functional adult.
  - It cleans the floors well enough, provided you aren't expecting a miracle.
  - The battery life is decent, though it won't be winning any endurance awards.
  - It’s a standard vacuum that does exactly what it says on the box, nothing more.
  - I’ve seen more suction power from a cheap straw in a thick milkshake.
  """,
  system_prompt = "Summarize the reviews into one sentence",
  model = "gemma3:1b"
)

