# %% [markdown]
# ## 2.3 Extraction
# 
# Extraction comes into play when we use the LLM to identify and retrieve important information from the input text. This helps in readability, and more importantly is needed for reliably passing data downstream into APIs, function calls, or sub-agents.
# 
# More specifically, we will be discussing the following strategies:
# - JSON Mode
# - Few-shot
# - Schema
# - Combined

# %% [markdown]
# ### 2.3.1 JSON Mode
# 
# We extract key features from a text and place them inside of a JSON object.

# %%
ChatWrapper(
  user_prompt = "I have been using this CleanPro-5000 vacuum cleaner recently. It broke down after it cleaned up spilled juice.",
  system_prompt = """Based on the user message extract information for the following json
```json
{
  "item": "string",
  "category": "string",
  "issue": "string",
  "time_used": "string",
  "discount_code": "string"
}
```
""",
  options = {'num_predict': 100}, # just to keep it brief
  model = "gemma3:1b"
)

