# 
# # <b> Observations </b>
# The responses were varied, and sometimes deviated from the given formatting. Aside from this, the LLM successfully categorized the ticket at a 92% confidence level.
# <br>
# 
# # <b> Analysis </b>
# It was imperative to fine tune the output formatting as the LLM kept on trying to revise and output slightly different from the given output. This may be due to the sheer amount of open-ended specifications given in a single prompt, requiring a much more verbose, streamlined and concise prompt in order to not confuse the LLM.
# <br>
# 
# # <b> Conclusions </b>
# This exercise highlighted the importance of structuring your prompts in order to deliver a specific business requirement. Variations in their responses can be fine tuned using different sampling parameters and additional information, structured through the use of classification, summarization, and extraction techniques. When all used in conjunction, this can effectively simulate simple-output dynamic response systems that can execute on different requirements and domains.
